{"lemma":"حَرْبَيْ","slug":"حَرْبَيْ","root":"ح.ر.ب","root_slug":"ح-ر-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ر-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حَرْب","root":"حرب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n7529","n7533","n7534","n7535"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be enraged, to be furious, to be angry"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"war","tags":["countable","uncountable"],"examples":[{"text":"تَتْرُكُ ٱلْحُرُوبُ أَثَرًا طَوِيلَ ٱلْأَمَدِ عَلَى ٱلْمُجْتَمَعَاتِ ٱلْمُتَضَرِّرَةِ.","english":"Wars leave a long-lasting impact on affected communities."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"warfare","tags":["countable","uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَرِبَ (ḥariba) (form I)","tags":["countable","form-of","noun-from-verb","uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rage","tags":["countable","uncountable"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *x̣arb-. Cognate with Biblical Hebrew חֶרֶב (ḥɛ́rɛḇ, “sword”).\n\nFrom Proto-Semitic *x̣arb-. Feminine because it meant a tool in Proto-Semitic, namely a blade."},"ipa":["/ħa.ri.ba/","/ħarb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n7529","headword_ar":"حرّب","root":"Hrb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHoriybN","text_ar":"تَحْرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sharpened"},{"kind":"text","text":"a spearhead. (S, K.) ―         -b2-  (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He angered:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"angered violently:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he provoked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exasperated."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA.) And it is said to signify (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He acquainted"},{"kind":"text","text":"a person"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a thing that angered him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but where it is said to have this meaning, it is accord. to one reading with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"j","text_ar":"ج"},{"kind":"text","text":"and hemzeh [in the places of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H","text_ar":"ح"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","K"]},{"entry_id":"n7533","headword_ar":"حَرْبٌ","root":"Hrb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"War, battle, fight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conflict;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"silomN","text_ar":"سِلْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) consisting, first, in"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shooting arrows, one at another;"},{"kind":"text","text":"then, in"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thrusting, one at another, with spears;"},{"kind":"text","text":"then, in"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"combating one another with swords;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and then, in"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grappling and struggling together:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Suh, TA:) it is [generally] fem.; (S, L Msb;) but its dim. is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HurayobN","text_ar":"حُرَيْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Kh, S, L, Msb,) contr. to rule, (L, Msb,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*urayoEN","text_ar":"ذُرَيْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quwayosN","text_ar":"قُوَيْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"furayosN","text_ar":"فُرَيْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a fem. sense, (L,) because originally an inf. n. [of which the verb ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Haraba","text_ar":"حَرَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":") seems not to have been used as meaning “ he waged, or contended in, war ”], (El-Mázinee, S,) or in order that it may not be confounded with the dim. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarobapN","text_ar":"حَرْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) Seer makes its origin to be the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarobN","text_ar":"حَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which, however, is originally an inf. n.: (L:) sometimes it is masc.; (IAar, Mbr, S, Msb, K;) but this is extr.: (L:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuruwbN","text_ar":"حُرُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqaEato bayonahumo HarobN","text_ar":"وَقَعَتْ بَيْنَهُمْ حَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"War happened between them"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAmati AlHarobu EalaY saAqK","text_ar":"قَامَتِ الحَرْبُ عَلَى سَاقٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The war,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"battle, became vehement, so that safety from destruction was difficult of attainment."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And making it masc., as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qitaAlN","text_ar":"قِتَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarobN $adiydN","text_ar":"حَرْبٌ شَدِيدٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A vehement fight"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"battle."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu HarobK","text_ar":"اِبْنُ حَرْبٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A warrior:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bnY","text_ar":"بنى"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aibonu AlHarobi","text_ar":"اِبْنُ الحَرْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the warrior;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he who suffices for war, and who defends."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb in that art.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAru AlHarobi","text_ar":"دَارُ الحَرْبِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The country,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"countries, of the unbelievers,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"those called by the Muslims"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the polytheists,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between whom and the Muslims there is not peace."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K.) In the saying of Aboo- Haneefeh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAnato mak~apu A_i*o *`Aka HarobFA","text_ar":"كَانَتْ مَكَّةُ اـِذْ ذٰاكَ حَرْبًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", the meaning is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAra HarobK","text_ar":"دَارَ حَرْبٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mekkeh was at that time a place of which the people were at war with the Muslims"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh.)       -A2-  It is also an epithet; originally an inf. n. (L.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN HarobN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ حَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) [in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaribN","text_ar":"حَرِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but it is] like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadolN","text_ar":"عَدْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man vehement in war, and courageous;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miHorabN","text_ar":"مِحْرَبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miHoraAbN","text_ar":"مِحْرَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miHorabN","text_ar":"مِحْرَبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a man of wars;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a man of war,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miHoraAbN","text_ar":"مِحْرَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a known, experienced warrior."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) [Being originally an inf. n.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarobN","text_ar":"حَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as an epithet is used in the same form as masc. and fem. and sing. and pl.: (K:) so that one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN HarobN","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ حَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawomN","text_ar":"قَوْمٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarobN","text_ar":"حَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawomN miHorabapN","text_ar":"قَوْمٌ مِحْرَبَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An enemy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) whether, or not, actually at war. (K.) So in the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaA HarobN limano","text_ar":"اَنَا حَرْبٌ لِمَنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaArabanaYi","text_ar":"حَارَبَنَىِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I am an enemy to him who wars with me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who is an enemy to me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Harobu fulaAnK","text_ar":"حَرْبُ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is the enemy of such a one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) Some hold that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarobN","text_ar":"حَرْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a pl. [or rather a quasi-pl. n.] of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAribN","text_ar":"حَارِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHaAribN","text_ar":"مُحَارِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Suh","TA","Kh","S","L","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n7534","headword_ar":"حَرَبٌ","root":"Hrb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hariba","text_ar":"حَرِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, Mgh, Msb.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAHarabaA","text_ar":"وَاحَرَبَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an ejaculation expressive of grief, lamentation, or regret, [meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Alas, my spoliation!"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my loss!"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"my grief!"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (ISd, Mgh, TA,) used in an absolute manner, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA A^asafaA","text_ar":"وَا اَسَفَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (ISd, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA A^asafaA","text_ar":"يَا اَسَفَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Harabahu","text_ar":"حَرَبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ he despoiled him of his wealth, or property: ” (K:) [or from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hariba","text_ar":"حَرِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.:] or it originated from the fact that Harb the son of Umeiyeh, when any one died, used to ask his family what they required to expend on the occasion, and used to supply them therewith; (TA;) and when he himself died, the people of Mekkeh and its neighbourhood bewailed him, saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA HarobaA","text_ar":"وَا حَرْبَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Th, K, * TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA HarobaAho","text_ar":"وَا حَرْبَاهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Alas for Harb!"},{"kind":"text","text":"] and then they changed the expression to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA HarabaA","text_ar":"وَا حَرَبَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Th, K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAHarabaAho","text_ar":"وَاحَرَبَاهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and it"},{"kind":"page_break","n":541},{"kind":"text","text":"became used in the case of bewailing any person who was dear, and in the cases of other calamities: but this account of the origin did not please ISd. (TA.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Perdition. destruction,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"death."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 158.)"}],"source_refs":["ISd","Mgh","TA","K","Th"]},{"entry_id":"n7535","headword_ar":"حَرِبٌ","root":"Hrb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HariybN","text_ar":"حَرِيبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Angry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"violently angry:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) applied to a man and to a lion. (S, A.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalibN","text_ar":"كَلِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Affected with canine madness"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HarobaY","text_ar":"حَرْبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalobaY","text_ar":"كَلْبَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", but unknown to Az in this sense except in one instance. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["A","S","K"]}]}}